The paper discusses the verification of software behavior models, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also proposes an automated mapping approach to create formal specifications, which involves programming language concepts (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The use of formal verification techniques also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
